source.body: Subject: Add a function that can hide columns in workbooks without breaking metrics |Original Zendesk ID: 41186 | Customer marked ticket severity (if blank, then severity was not specified): s3_-_low_impact_issue_or_enhacement/feature_request | Message: ---------------------------------------------- Vladimir Turkin, Jan 19, 2026, 02:33 While searching for a way to hide columns in a data model and prevent them from being selected in dependent workbooks, while still allowing metrics to function, I discovered that this is not possible. Why would I want to do this? Because we have a large number of columns, and these columns offer no value on their own without aggregation. This means we want to provide end users with metrics and hide columns completely. This would make the use of data models much less confusing and more organized. Instead, we now have, for example, 50 columns and 50 or more metrics, both of which can be used simultaneously. 1. The first option is Column Security: I create a data model In this data model, I define metrics Then I apply the column security No one can view. If I now create a workbook based on the data model, I can no longer select the columns, just as I wanted. But I also cannot use the metrics I created because they are based on columns that are part of the Column Security. The name No one can view for Column Security is therefore not ideal. View is not entirely correct in this context; instead, restrict or something similar is applied. 2. The second option is to hide the columns in the data model. However, the columns are still selectable in the workbook. They are just not selected by default. So they are still usable and visible. They are not really hidden, just 'unselected by default'. Feature request: Please add a 'Hide' option on the Data Model level which is inherited to workbooks and which actually hides columns without restricting the metrics that use them. It should just be a simple, but real, 'hide', not a 'restrict'. Attachment(s): Option2_Hide_Sigma_Feature_Request.png - https://support.sigmacomputing.com/attachments/token/svRfhgBOKUn3tN0pGYrCxWDD9/?name=Option2_Hide_Sigma_Feature_Request.pngOption1_Restrict_Sigma_Feature_Request.png.png - https://support.sigmacomputing.com/attachments/token/k9JS3QEohcRH1KcnkyLfkkPTw/?name=Option1_Restrict_Sigma_Feature_Request.png.png
